Let $a_n$ be sequence of positive numbers ($n = 1, 2, ...$, $a_n != 0$ for
all $n$), and let $b_n = (a_1 + ... + a_n)/n$, the average of the first $n$
numbers of the sequence. Suppose $display(sum_(n=1)^(infinity)
(1)/(a_n))$ is a convergent series. Prove that
$display(sum_(n=1)^(infinity) (1)/(b_n))$ is also a convergent series.
